{"id":"ghtml-yzm","title":"Epic: package-restructure","description":"Restructure ghtml internals to support multiple codegen backends. Phases: (1) AST cleanup - generic modifiers, type renames, (2) Parser split - extract lexer, (3) Target architecture - dispatch system, CLI flag. See .claude/specs/package-restructure/ for full spec.","notes":"Spec: .claude/specs/package-restructure","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","owner":"burakcorekcioglu@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-02-07T10:59:38.649699+01:00","created_by":"Burak Corekcioglu","updated_at":"2026-02-07T11:58:47.916968+01:00","closed_at":"2026-02-07T11:58:47.916968+01:00","close_reason":"All tasks completed","labels":["epic","spec:package-restructure"]}
{"id":"ghtml-yzm.1","title":"REQ-001: Change EventAttr to use generic modifiers List(String)","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","owner":"burakcorekcioglu@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-02-07T10:59:49.870568+01:00","created_by":"Burak Corekcioglu","updated_at":"2026-02-07T11:09:54.129749+01:00","closed_at":"2026-02-07T11:09:54.129749+01:00","close_reason":"Closed","labels":["pr:17","task"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ghtml-yzm.1","depends_on_id":"ghtml-yzm","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-07T10:59:49.871377+01:00","created_by":"Burak Corekcioglu"}],"comments":[{"id":7,"issue_id":"ghtml-yzm.1","author":"Burak Corekcioglu","text":"## Phase 1: AST Cleanup (REQ-001)\n\nChange EventAttr to use generic modifiers instead of Lustre-specific boolean flags.\n\n### What to change\n- In types.gleam: `EventAttr(event, handler, prevent_default: Bool, stop_propagation: Bool)` → `EventAttribute(event, handler, modifiers: List(String))`\n- In parser.gleam: Where modifiers are parsed from `.prevent` and `.stop` syntax, produce `[\"prevent\", \"stop\"]` list instead of setting booleans\n- In codegen.gleam: Interpret modifiers list → wrap with `event.prevent_default()` / `event.stop_propagation()`\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n- EventAttr uses modifiers: List(String)\n- Parser produces [\"prevent\"] for .prevent, [\"stop\"] for .stop, [\"prevent\", \"stop\"] for .prevent.stop\n- Modifier order preserved from template syntax\n- All existing event modifier tests pass with updated assertions\n- just check passes\n\n### Spec: .claude/specs/package-restructure/requirements.md REQ-001","created_at":"2026-02-07T10:00:09Z"}]}
{"id":"ghtml-yzm.2","title":"REQ-002: Rename Attr types to Attribute (StaticAttr→StaticAttribute etc.)","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","owner":"burakcorekcioglu@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-02-07T10:59:51.431279+01:00","created_by":"Burak Corekcioglu","updated_at":"2026-02-07T11:14:49.186902+01:00","closed_at":"2026-02-07T11:14:49.186902+01:00","close_reason":"Closed","labels":["pr:18","task"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ghtml-yzm.2","depends_on_id":"ghtml-yzm","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-07T10:59:51.432116+01:00","created_by":"Burak Corekcioglu"},{"issue_id":"ghtml-yzm.2","depends_on_id":"ghtml-yzm.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-07T11:00:48.974896+01:00","created_by":"Burak Corekcioglu"}],"comments":[{"id":8,"issue_id":"ghtml-yzm.2","author":"Burak Corekcioglu","text":"## Phase 1: AST Cleanup (REQ-002)\n\nRename abbreviated type names for clarity across multi-backend audience.\n\n### Renames\n| Current | New |\n|---------|-----|\n| Attr | Attribute |\n| StaticAttr | StaticAttribute |\n| DynamicAttr | DynamicAttribute |\n| EventAttr | EventAttribute |\n| BooleanAttr | BooleanAttribute |\n\n### Scope\n- types.gleam: type definitions\n- parser.gleam: all constructor references\n- codegen.gleam: all pattern matches and constructors\n- All test files referencing these types\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n- All type names use full words\n- All references updated across parser, codegen, and tests\n- No functional changes — rename only\n- just check passes\n\n### Spec: .claude/specs/package-restructure/requirements.md REQ-002","created_at":"2026-02-07T10:00:13Z"}]}
{"id":"ghtml-yzm.3","title":"REQ-003+004: Extract lexer module from parser and slim down parser.gleam","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","owner":"burakcorekcioglu@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-02-07T10:59:52.747389+01:00","created_by":"Burak Corekcioglu","updated_at":"2026-02-07T11:23:59.793274+01:00","closed_at":"2026-02-07T11:23:59.793274+01:00","close_reason":"Closed","labels":["pr:19","task"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ghtml-yzm.3","depends_on_id":"ghtml-yzm","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-07T10:59:52.748212+01:00","created_by":"Burak Corekcioglu"},{"issue_id":"ghtml-yzm.3","depends_on_id":"ghtml-yzm.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-07T11:00:49.846433+01:00","created_by":"Burak Corekcioglu"}],"comments":[{"id":9,"issue_id":"ghtml-yzm.3","author":"Burak Corekcioglu","text":"## Phase 2: Parser Split (REQ-003 + REQ-004)\n\nExtract tokenize() and all supporting tokenization functions from parser.gleam (1713 lines) into a dedicated lexer.gleam module.\n\n### What moves to lexer.gleam\n- pub fn tokenize(input) → Result(List(Token), List(ParseError))\n- All tokenization helpers: token recognition, brace balancing, {{ / }} escapes, position tracking, attribute parsing\n\n### What stays in parser.gleam\n- pub fn parse(input) → calls lexer.tokenize() then build_ast()\n- pub fn build_ast(tokens) → stack-based AST construction\n- Import/params extraction\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n- lexer.gleam exists with tokenize() as public function\n- parser.gleam imports ghtml/lexer and delegates tokenization\n- parser.gleam is significantly smaller (only AST construction)\n- build_ast() remains public for tools needing token-level access\n- All existing tokenizer and parser tests pass\n- just check passes\n\n### Spec: .claude/specs/package-restructure/requirements.md REQ-003, REQ-004","created_at":"2026-02-07T10:00:19Z"}]}
{"id":"ghtml-yzm.4","title":"REQ-005+006: Add Target type and create target/ directory structure","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","owner":"burakcorekcioglu@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-02-07T10:59:54.124649+01:00","created_by":"Burak Corekcioglu","updated_at":"2026-02-07T11:27:52.648829+01:00","closed_at":"2026-02-07T11:27:52.648829+01:00","close_reason":"Closed","labels":["pr:20","task"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ghtml-yzm.4","depends_on_id":"ghtml-yzm","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-07T10:59:54.125449+01:00","created_by":"Burak Corekcioglu"},{"issue_id":"ghtml-yzm.4","depends_on_id":"ghtml-yzm.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-07T11:00:51.186823+01:00","created_by":"Burak Corekcioglu"}],"comments":[{"id":10,"issue_id":"ghtml-yzm.4","author":"Burak Corekcioglu","text":"## Phase 3: Target Architecture (REQ-005 + REQ-006)\n\nAdd the Target type and create the target/ directory.\n\n### What to do\n1. Add to types.gleam:\n```gleam\npub type Target {\n  Lustre\n  // Future: StringTree, String, Reactive\n}\n```\n\n2. Create directory: src/ghtml/target/\n3. Create placeholder target/lustre.gleam (actual logic moves in next task)\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n- Target type defined in types.gleam with Lustre variant\n- src/ghtml/target/ directory exists\n- Type is extensible for future targets\n- just check passes\n\n### Spec: .claude/specs/package-restructure/requirements.md REQ-005, REQ-006","created_at":"2026-02-07T10:00:23Z"}]}
{"id":"ghtml-yzm.5","title":"REQ-007+008: Move Lustre codegen to target/lustre.gleam and extract shared utils","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","owner":"burakcorekcioglu@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-02-07T10:59:55.650924+01:00","created_by":"Burak Corekcioglu","updated_at":"2026-02-07T11:35:28.541906+01:00","closed_at":"2026-02-07T11:35:28.541906+01:00","close_reason":"Closed","labels":["pr:21","task"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ghtml-yzm.5","depends_on_id":"ghtml-yzm","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-07T10:59:55.651817+01:00","created_by":"Burak Corekcioglu"},{"issue_id":"ghtml-yzm.5","depends_on_id":"ghtml-yzm.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-07T11:00:52.381261+01:00","created_by":"Burak Corekcioglu"}],"comments":[{"id":11,"issue_id":"ghtml-yzm.5","author":"Burak Corekcioglu","text":"## Phase 3: Target Architecture (REQ-007 + REQ-008)\n\nThe big move: extract all Lustre-specific code from codegen.gleam into target/lustre.gleam, and identify shared utilities.\n\n### What moves to target/lustre.gleam\n- known_attributes constant (21 HTML→Lustre attr mappings)\n- boolean_attributes constant\n- Event handler mapping (click→event.on_click etc.)\n- Event modifier interpretation (\"prevent\"→event.prevent_default() wrapping)\n- Lustre import generation (lustre/element, lustre/event, etc.)\n- All Lustre-specific node generation (html.div, element, keyed.fragment, text, etc.)\n\n### What stays as shared in codegen.gleam\n- escape_string(), normalize_whitespace(), is_blank()\n- void_elements list, is_custom_element(), is_void_element()\n- AST analysis helpers: template_has_events(), template_has_attrs(), template_has_each(), etc.\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n- All Lustre-specific code in target/lustre.gleam\n- Output is byte-for-byte identical to current implementation\n- All existing codegen tests pass (re-pointed to target/lustre)\n- No Lustre references remain in codegen.gleam\n- just check passes\n\n### Spec: .claude/specs/package-restructure/requirements.md REQ-007, REQ-008","created_at":"2026-02-07T10:00:29Z"}]}
{"id":"ghtml-yzm.6","title":"REQ-009: Refactor codegen.gleam into thin target dispatcher","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","owner":"burakcorekcioglu@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-02-07T10:59:56.778499+01:00","created_by":"Burak Corekcioglu","updated_at":"2026-02-07T11:43:35.660339+01:00","closed_at":"2026-02-07T11:43:35.660339+01:00","close_reason":"Closed","labels":["pr:22","task"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ghtml-yzm.6","depends_on_id":"ghtml-yzm","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-07T10:59:56.779304+01:00","created_by":"Burak Corekcioglu"},{"issue_id":"ghtml-yzm.6","depends_on_id":"ghtml-yzm.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-07T11:00:53.261412+01:00","created_by":"Burak Corekcioglu"}],"comments":[{"id":12,"issue_id":"ghtml-yzm.6","author":"Burak Corekcioglu","text":"## Phase 3: Target Architecture (REQ-009)\n\nRefactor codegen.gleam from containing all codegen logic to being a thin dispatcher that routes to the appropriate target.\n\n### Target state of codegen.gleam\n```gleam\npub fn generate(template, source_path, hash, target) -\u003e String {\n  case target {\n    Lustre -\u003e lustre.generate(template, source_path, hash)\n  }\n}\n// + shared utility functions\n```\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n- codegen.generate() dispatches by Target value\n- Dispatcher contains no codegen logic (only routing + shared utils)\n- Adding new target requires: new file in target/, new Target variant, new case branch\n- just check passes\n\n### Spec: .claude/specs/package-restructure/requirements.md REQ-009","created_at":"2026-02-07T10:00:34Z"}]}
{"id":"ghtml-yzm.7","title":"REQ-010+011: Add --target CLI flag and thread Target through pipeline/watcher","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","owner":"burakcorekcioglu@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-02-07T10:59:58.662505+01:00","created_by":"Burak Corekcioglu","updated_at":"2026-02-07T11:52:16.67419+01:00","closed_at":"2026-02-07T11:52:16.67419+01:00","close_reason":"Closed","labels":["pr:23","task"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ghtml-yzm.7","depends_on_id":"ghtml-yzm","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-07T10:59:58.66328+01:00","created_by":"Burak Corekcioglu"},{"issue_id":"ghtml-yzm.7","depends_on_id":"ghtml-yzm.6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-07T11:00:54.964332+01:00","created_by":"Burak Corekcioglu"}],"comments":[{"id":13,"issue_id":"ghtml-yzm.7","author":"Burak Corekcioglu","text":"## Phase 3: Target Architecture (REQ-010 + REQ-011)\n\nAdd --target CLI flag and thread Target parameter through the entire pipeline.\n\n### CLI changes (ghtml.gleam)\n- Parse --target=\u003cname\u003e from CLI args, default to lustre\n- Invalid target → error with valid options list\n- Pass Target to codegen.generate() and watcher\n\n### Pipeline changes\n- codegen.generate() signature: add target parameter\n- ghtml.gleam process_file(): accept and pass Target\n- watcher.gleam: accept Target in start_watching(), pass through to codegen\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n- --target flag parsed, default lustre\n- Invalid targets produce clear error message\n- Target flows through entire pipeline\n- Watch mode respects target flag\n- just check passes\n\n### Spec: .claude/specs/package-restructure/requirements.md REQ-010, REQ-011","created_at":"2026-02-07T10:00:39Z"}]}
{"id":"ghtml-yzm.8","title":"REQ-012+013: Verify backwards compatibility and migrate test suite","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","owner":"burakcorekcioglu@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-02-07T10:59:59.812144+01:00","created_by":"Burak Corekcioglu","updated_at":"2026-02-07T11:58:47.617711+01:00","closed_at":"2026-02-07T11:58:47.617711+01:00","close_reason":"Closed","labels":["pr:24","task"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ghtml-yzm.8","depends_on_id":"ghtml-yzm","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-07T10:59:59.812969+01:00","created_by":"Burak Corekcioglu"},{"issue_id":"ghtml-yzm.8","depends_on_id":"ghtml-yzm.7","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-07T11:00:55.814869+01:00","created_by":"Burak Corekcioglu"}],"comments":[{"id":14,"issue_id":"ghtml-yzm.8","author":"Burak Corekcioglu","text":"## Cross-Cutting (REQ-012 + REQ-013)\n\nFinal verification: backwards compatibility and test coverage.\n\n### Backwards Compatibility (REQ-012)\n- gleam run -m ghtml with no args produces identical output\n- All examples build and produce same output\n- No changes required in downstream projects\n\n### Test Migration (REQ-013)\n- Lexer tests import from ghtml/lexer\n- Parser tests import from ghtml/parser\n- Codegen tests work through dispatcher or directly test target/lustre\n- New tests for: target dispatch, invalid target error, generic event modifiers\n- Integration tests verify end-to-end pipeline with target flag\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n- just check passes\n- just e2e passes\n- just check-examples passes\n- All test files use correct imports for new module boundaries\n\n### Spec: .claude/specs/package-restructure/requirements.md REQ-012, REQ-013","created_at":"2026-02-07T10:00:43Z"}]}
